<br>
Oh wait, my mistake ... chuckling ... how silly of me, you speak Common.  As I started saying ....<br>
<br>
I am Pleides.  I guess my story begins when I was but a wee child.  For some unknown reason, my mother apparently didn't want or couldn't handle me.  As such, I was given to the Temple to raise me.  I really don't know much of her; rich or poor, pretty or ugly, common or noble.  However, I learned from the Brothers that it really doesn't matter.  I am my own person.  Although I've begun to doubt that lately too.<br>
<br>
You see, I've found that I really haven't seen anything of the world outside of Rivervale.  And little of Rivervale at that, outside of the Temple.  I don't know anything about the *real* world, and I'm dying to know if my life has the meaning that I've been told it does.  I've heard tales from visitors to the Temple of the world outside, but I have to believe that most of them are exaggerations.<br>
<br>
Honestly, how can anyone believe stories of flying lions?  Or giant spiders bigger than those humans?  Or over large human looking beings, bigger than mountains?  It's just so inconceivable.  I know what you're thinking.  That doesn't mean what I think it means.  But it's true; they HAVE to be exaggerations.<br>
<br>
So, I have made the decision that I have to see the rest of the world for myself.  When I informed the Brethren of my decision and they saw my resolution in that, they have offered me assistance in my destiny.  They are taught me the secrets of their order: how to maintain calm in any situation, how to channel the forces of Fizzlethorpe Bristlebane's grace to help affect life here, how to act in the best interest of myself, the world, and, of course, in the best interest of Bristlebane.<br>
<br>
Armed with this new knowledge, I and ready to set out.  Easily, I find myself totally unequipped for this life outside of the Temple.  I don't mean physically; I mean mentally and emotionally.  So much turmoil and bustle.  How could ANYONE live like this??  I have spent the better part of this week wandering and just learning about my own home town.  After living here for so long, I'm amazed at how little I know of my own people.  And the STRANGERS!  So many.  So many kinds.  Tall, short, big, little, broad, thin, light, dark.  This an adventure in itself!<br>
<br>
Finding my way through the mountain pass that protects Rivervale, I enter the woods, as I begin my look into the world.  Dark and scary.  I almost turn back.  But that would admit defeat to Fizzlethorpe and to myself and my destiny.  And I can't do that.<br>
