<br>
My mother, the charismatic Millea, was a bard of the highest cast. In an attempt to take out evil she joined with her brothers and sisters to raid the city of Neriak, the battle was long and bloody, the humans couldnt stand up to the power of the dark elves. Millea was badly injured and left to die by her fellow humans.<br>
    A dark elf necromancer saw her laying on the street and dragged her into his house in the third gate. He healed her wounds so that she would not bleed to death. He kept her as a maid for several years, and used her in anyway he could. Eventually Millea got pregnant and felt forced to tell her master, the necromancer couldnt come up with a solution, Innoruuk would not allow this.. so he threw her out, back to the street.<br>
    Millea went back to Freeport to find her family which she eventually did. She told them nothing about what had happened to her, but she was unable to hide her pregnancy, and her family got curious. When I was eventually born Millea tried to hide me away from the family, but the old woman who gave birth to me told Millea's father about my purple eyes and some other dark elf features which where unmistakable.<br>
    Millea was hung for her actions on the day of my 4th birthday. The family refused to take responsibility for me. But my fathers sister, Itera, heard the story about my mother, she looked for me and finally found me in the secret passages of Freeport. She took me to Neriak, where she lived after being banished from Freeport for the murder on a militiaman, and taught me the little she knew of my mothers proffession and mixed it with her own rogue skills.<br>
    The day came when I was old enough to take care of myself and leave the house where I had been hidden from the world. I sneaked out of Neriak, barely escaping the blade of Khazan Punox. I was a puzzled child, I did not know what to belive, what would be my way of life? The &quot;good&quot; had turned theire backs on me in my time of need. I was a outcast, not liked anywhere, the dark elfs had showed me theire ways, but they still did not accept me, I could not turn to them...<br>
    While wandering through the empty plains of Karana I caught up with a mysterious man, I never knew his name, but he calmed my stirred consience. He taught me an alternative way of life, the way of a Setite. I needed no one, I could take care of myself, if I only followed his ways and charished my fellow Setites. He took me to his crypt where he let me meet some others, I was puzzled once again, these were people of all races and crafts, and they all had the same beliefs? This must be the life for me, I was to become a Setite.<br>
    Now I thought that this was the end of my suffering, I could take care of myself, I knew what to do. Yeah right.. I was out hunting by myself one winters night when I strange dark elf suddenly appeared, I cant remember much more of the incident, but I woke up three days later knowing that something had happend to me. The following year I gave birth to my daughter, I gave her the name Set told me, Khemi, meaning Overthrower. I still do not know who her father is. She showed her arcane powers early and I did my best to teach her the way of a wizard, with alot of help from my wonderful wife, the dark elf wizardress Darka.<br>
    Now You know the story of my pityful life, I do not know why you should have this knowledge.. but my Master told me to share my life with the rest of you, so here it is.<br>
    As long as we are out there, You will be frightend, You will be corrupted, You will be sacrificed for Our beliefs. <p>Flexure Graverobber, 52 cleric -
